 -----------
 identifierForVendor
An alphanumeric string that uniquely identifies a device to the appâ€™s vendor. (read-only)

@property(nonatomic, readonly, retain) NSUUID *identifierForVendor
Discussion
The value of this property is the same for apps that come from the same vendor running on the same device. A different value is returned for apps on the same device that come from different vendors, and for apps on different devices regardless of vendor.

Availability
Available in iOS 6.0 and later.
Declared In
UIDevice.h
----------------
The UITableViewController class allows you to add a built-in refresh control (UIRefreshControl) to reload the table contents.
